<p itemprop="description">An interaction designer creates intuitive and accessible user experiences for digital government services. They understand user needs, design comprehensive interaction flows, and work collaboratively with multidisciplinary teams to deliver user-centred solutions that help citizens complete their tasks efficiently.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Design comprehensive user experiences and interaction flows for complex services</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Create detailed wireframes, prototypes, and design specifications</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Conduct user research and usability testing to inform design decisions</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Ensure designs meet accessibility standards and inclusive design principles</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Collaborate with content designers, developers, and product managers</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Design and maintain component libraries and design systems</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Iterate designs based on user feedback, analytics, and research insights</li>
    </ul>
</section>

